Domain:  Physics
Topic:   E = mc²
Formula: E = mc²
Note:    Mass-energy equivalence; foundation of nuclear physics

Domain:  Physics
Topic:   Gravitational Force
Formula: F = Gm1m2/r²
Note:    Universal gravitation between all masses

Domain:  Physics
Topic:   Newton's Second Law
Formula: F = ma
Note:    Force equals mass times acceleration; classical mechanics

Domain:  Mathematics
Topic:   Central Limit Theorem
Formula: Sample means → normal distribution
Note:    Foundation of statistical inference and polling

Domain:  Physics
Topic:   2nd Law of Thermodynamics
Formula: ΔS ≥ 0
Note:    Entropy always increases in isolated systems

============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Binomial Theorem
Branch:       Algebra
Formula:      (a+b)^n = sum of C(n,k) a^k b^(n-k)
Applications: Probability, statistics, polynomial algebra
Discoverer:   Newton/Pascal (1665)

Theorem/Law:  Taylor Series
Branch:       Calculus
Formula:      f(x) = sum of f^n(a)/n! * (x-a)^n
Applications: Numerical computation, signal processing
Discoverer:   Brook Taylor (1715)

Theorem/Law:  Prime Number Theorem
Branch:       Number Theory
Formula:      π(n) ~ n/ln(n)
Applications: Cryptography, algorithm analysis
Discoverer:   Hadamard/de la VP (1896)

